<h1>Hey, {{ firstName if firstName else '{{first_name}}' }},</h1>

<p>We’re excited to have you at RevolutionUC! Because you’re under 18, there is some extra information you need to know to get ready. Following these guidelines is mandatory and necessary for compliance with university guidelines. Please share this document with your parent/guardian.</p>

<p><strong>Communication Information</strong><br />
Parents/guardians will be able contact hackathon organizers with questions or concerns during the event. The primary contact for questions related to minors at the event is Lina Kaval, who can be reached at (513) 550-3857. Our backup contact is Brandon Starcheus, who can be reached at (614) 915-9149. Questions can also be asked prior to the event via email at info@revolutionuc.com. Parents/Guardians are also expected to supervise their participant during the event.</p>

<p><strong>Waiver and Release Forms</strong>
You can view and download the required waiver and release forms at this link. Each form (total of 3) must be completed and signed by a parent/guardian - these must be completed and emailed to this email (info@revolutionuc.com) before February 20th. These forms are mandatory in order to be allowed to participate in RevolutionUC.</p>

<p>The three forms are the Minors Waiver, Liability Release Form, and Photo Release Form. Please make sure to fill out these forms; it is not the same waiver that is given to over 18 participants at the time of registration. Submission of the waiver and forms at check-in is mandatory for participation.</p>

<p>In the event of an emergency, we will notify your primary emergency contact. If we cannot reach your primary contact, we will notify your secondary emergency contact.</p>

<p>
